            // The transform is only valid if the fabs does not have nnan. \
            // If it has nnan, a SNaN input to fabs will result in a poison, \
            // which will propagate through the fcmp, making the result poison. \
            // The original code would return false in this case because the \
            // '\''fcmp ord'\'' would be false. \
            if (auto *Fabs = dyn_cast<CallInst>(FCmp1->getOperand(0))) \
              if (Fabs->hasNoNaNs()) \
                return nullptr; \
' llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineCasts.cpp
```
This seems correct. I'll apply this change.

```bash
sed -i '/FCmp1->getPredicate() == CmpInst::FCMP_OEQ) {/a \
            if (auto *Fabs = dyn_cast<CallInst>(FCmp1->getOperand(0))) {\
